<section class="elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-1d18ae32 elementor-section-height-min-height elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-items-middle" data-element_type="section" data-id="1d18ae32" data-settings='{"background_background":"classic"}'>
<div class="elementor-background-overlay"></div>
<div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">
<div class="elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-1fc5c842" data-element_type="column" data-id="1fc5c842">
<div class="elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-2b0834a8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer" data-element_type="widget" data-id="2b0834a8" data-widget_type="spacer.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<div class="elementor-spacer">
<div class="elementor-spacer-inner"></div>

<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-7e075037 elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-element_type="widget" data-id="7e075037" data-settings='{"motion_fx_motion_fx_scrolling":"yes","motion_fx_translateY_effect":"yes","motion_fx_translateY_speed":{"unit":"px","size":0.5,"sizes":[]},"_animation":"fadeInUp","_animation_delay":500,"motion_fx_translateY_affectedRange":{"unit":"%","size":"","sizes":{"start":0,"end":100}},"motion_fx_devices":["desktop","tablet","mobile"]}' data-widget_type="heading.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<h1 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">Privacy Policy</h1> </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-e8fcd63 elementor-section-height-min-height elementor-section-items-top elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default" data-element_type="section" data-id="e8fcd63">
<div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">
<div class="elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-852bafb" data-element_type="column" data-id="852bafb">
<div class="elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-3fdb5ca5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-element_type="widget" data-id="3fdb5ca5" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<p><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Last updated: December 17</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">th</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, 2020</span></em></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This Privacy Policy governs the manner in which KETOS collects, uses, maintains and discloses personal information about users (each, a “User”) of the </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">www.ketos.co</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website (the “Site”) and recipients of our emails. </span></p>
<p><b>How we collect information</b></p>
<p><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Information Users provide to us: </span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">When Users visit the Site, Users may provide information to us directly. For example, when a User:</span></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Requests a demo on the Site, we may collect information such as name, phone number, company, industry and email address. </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Places an order, we may collect the User’s name, email address, phone number, shipping and billing addresses, payment information, and information about the User’s purchase. </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Signs up for email updates, we may collect the User’s email address, name, company, and marketing preferences.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fills out a form, completes a survey, or contacts KETOS, we may collect the User’s name, email address, and contents of their communication.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Information collected automatically: </span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">We, our service providers, and our business partners may automatically collect information about Users and their computers or devices whenever they interact with our Site or emails. This information may include browser name, IP address, device identifier, operating system, general location information (such as city, state), and information about the User’s interactions with the Site or email, such as pages viewed and links clicked. This information is collected using cookies, browser web storage, web beacons, and similar technologies. </span></p>
<p><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Information we obtain from social media platforms:</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> We may maintain pages for KETOS on social media platforms, such as Facebook, Google, and Instagram. When Users visit or interact with our pages on those platforms, the platform provider’s privacy policy will apply to those interactions and their collection, use and processing of personal information. Users or the platforms may provide us with information through the platform, and we will treat such information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</span></p>
<p><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Information we obtain from other third parties</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">: We may receive personal information about Users from third-party sources where they have a right to provide us with this information. We may also obtain personal information from other third parties, such as marketing partners, and publicly available sources.</span></p>
<p><b>How we use collected information</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">KETOS may collect and use Users’ personal information for the following purposes:</span></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To run and operate our Site: We may need User information to, for example, display content on the Site correctly.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To improve customer service: Information a User provides helps us respond to customer service requests and support needs more efficiently.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To personalize User experience: We may use information about you to personalize our services, such as remembering your information so that you will not have to re-enter it during your visit or the next time you visit the site, and provide customized content and information.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To improve our Site: We may use feedback Users provide to improve our products and services.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To process orders or other transactions: We may use the information a User provides when placing an order to process and fulfill that order. </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To run a promotion, contest, or survey</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To send marketing emails. We may send you marketing emails as permitted by law. Users can opt out of these marketing emails as described in User Choices</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To communicate with Users. We may contact a User to send them notifications about their account and to respond to their inquiries, questions, and/or other requests. </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To post user testimonials and feedback: We may publish testimonials and comments from Users who have had positive experiences with KETOS. When we publish this content, we will identify our Users by their first name and last initial and may also indicate their home city. We will obtain the User’s consent prior to posting their name along with the testimonial. </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">For compliance, fraud prevention, and safety: We may use personal information and disclose it to law enforcement, government authorities, and private parties as we believe necessary or appropriate to: (a) protect our, a User’s or others’ rights, privacy, safety or property (including by making and defending legal claims); (b) enforce the terms and conditions that govern the Service; and (c) protect, investigate and deter against fraudulent, harmful, unauthorized, unethical or illegal activity; and (d) to comply with applicable laws, lawful requests, and legal process, such as to respond to subpoenas. </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">With consent: In some cases, we may specifically ask for consent to collect, use or share personal information and will collect, use or share such information in accordance with such authorizations.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To create anonymous data: We may create anonymous data from Users’ personal information. We make personal information into anonymous data by removing information that makes the data personally identifiable to a User. We may use this anonymous data and share it with third parties for any lawful business purposes, including to analyze and improve the service and promote our business.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b> </b></p>
<p><b>Sharing personal information</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We do not share personal information with third parties without User consent, except as described in this Privacy Policy:</span></p>
<ul>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">We may use third-party service providers to help us operate the Site or administer activities on our behalf, such as sending out surveys. We may share your information with these third parties for those limited purposes.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">We may share your information with our corporate parent, subsidiaries, and affiliates for purposes consistent with this Privacy Policy. </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">We use payment processing providers that provide secure processing services. Please note payment card details are not shared with us by the provider.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Like many companies online, KETOS works with advertising partners that rely on tracking technologies – such as cookies – to collect behavioral information about how Users use and interact with our Site and emails or other online services over time in order to perform tracking and marketing analytics or serve advertisements that are more likely to be of interest to you (“Interest-Based Advertisements”).  </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If a User has enabled features that connect the Site to a social media network (such as by sharing content via Facebook), we may disclose the personal information that the User authorized us to share. We do not control the third party’s use of personal information.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">We may disclose personal information to professional advisors, such as lawyers, bankers, auditors and insurers, where necessary for the professional services that they render to us.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">We may share personal information for the compliance, fraud prevention and safety purposes outlined above.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">We may sell, transfer or otherwise share some or all of our business or assets, including Users’ personal information, in connection with a business transaction (or potential business transaction) such as a corporate divestiture, merger, consolidation, acquisition, reorganization or sale of assets, or in the event of bankruptcy or dissolution. In such a case, we will make reasonable efforts to require the recipient to honor this Privacy Policy.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b> </b></p>
<p><b>User choices</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">All users have the following choices over their personal information:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Access or Update Account Information: If a User has registered for an account with us, the User may review and update certain personal information in their account profile by logging into the account.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Opt Out of Marketing Emails: If at any time a User would like to unsubscribe from receiving future marketing emails, we include detailed unsubscribe instructions at the bottom of each email or the User may contact us. We may continue to send service-related and other non-marketing emails. </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Interest-Based Advertisements: Users may limit the use of their information for Interest-Based Advertisements by companies participating in the Network Advertising Initiative by clicking </span><a href="https://www.networkadvertising.org/choices&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1576542844037000"><span style="font-weight: 400;">here</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or the Digital Advertising Alliance by clicking </span><a href="http://www.aboutads.info/choices&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1576542844038000"><span style="font-weight: 400;">here</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Some of our partners, like </span><a href="https://adssettings.google.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Google</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, may offer their own opt-out mechanism. </span></li>
<li aria-level="1" style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do Not Track: Some Internet browsers may be configured to send “Do Not Track” signals to the online services that you visit. We currently do not respond to “Do Not Track” or similar signals. Learn more </span><a href="https://allaboutdnt.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">here</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Choosing not to share your personal information. Where we are required by law to collect User information, or where we need personal information to provide the Service to the User, if a User does not provide this information when requested (or later asks to delete it), we may not be able to provide our services to the User. We will inform Users that information is necessary to receive the services by designating it as required at the time of collection or through other appropriate means.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b> </b></p>
<p><b>Third party websites</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Users may find advertising or other content on our Site that link to the sites and services of our partners, suppliers, advertisers, sponsors, licensors and other third parties. We do not control the content or links that appear on these sites and are not responsible for the practices employed by websites linked to or from our Site. In addition, these sites or services, including their content and links, may be constantly changing. These sites and services may have their own privacy policies and customer service policies that may differ materially from ours. Browsing and interaction on any other website, including websites which have a link to our Site, is subject to that website’s own terms and policies.</span></p>
<p><b>How we protect your information</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We have adopted data collection, storage and processing practices and security measures designed to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure or destruction of Users’ personal information.</span></p>
<p><b>Children</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Protecting the privacy of children is especially important. For that reason, we do not intentionally collect or maintain information from children under the age of 13, and no part of our website is directed to anyone under 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information of a child without the consent of the child’s parent or guardian as required by law, we will delete it. </span></p>
<p><b>Changes to this Privacy Policy</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">KETOS has the discretion to update this Privacy Policy at any time. If we make material changes to this Privacy Policy, we will notify Users by updating the date of this Privacy Policy and posting it on the Site. We may also provide notification of changes in another way that we believe is reasonably likely to reach Users, such as via e-mail (if a User has an account) or another manner through the Site. </span></p>
<p><b>Users outside the U.S.</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">KETOS is a US-based organization, and we apply U.S. law to our privacy practices. Wherever you are in the world, this Privacy Policy will apply to the information you provide to us or we collect when you visit the Site.</span></p>
<p><b>Contact us</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at [<a class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="b4dddad2dbf4dfd1c0dbc79ad7db" href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection">[email protected]</a>]. </span></p> </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
